From: Steffen Jaeckel <sjaeckel@suse.de>
Subject: kABI fix for ipvlan: Make the addrs_lock be per port
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI workaround
References: CVE-2026-23103 bsc#1257773

This is a kABI fix for upstream commit d3ba32162488 ("ipvlan:
Make the addrs_lock be per port") which moved the lock from the device
to the port and in order to restore kABI we have to re-introduce the now
unused lock. Also we put the lock of the port to the end of the struct
and hide it from the kABI checker.

This patch should not be required, since both, device and port, are managed
entirely inside the module, but since `ipvlan_count_rx()` is an exported
symbol, `ipvl_dev` and thereby `ipvl_port` are also part of kABI.

Signed-off-by: Steffen Jaeckel <sjaeckel@suse.de>
Reviewed-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/net/ipvlan/ipvlan.h | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ipvlan/ipvlan.h b/drivers/net/ipvlan/ipvlan.h
index befb61e00d07..8fbf3ee7596c 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ipvlan/ipvlan.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ipvlan/ipvlan.h
@@ -69,6 +69,7 @@ struct ipvl_dev {
 	DECLARE_BITMAP(mac_filters, IPVLAN_MAC_FILTER_SIZE);
 	netdev_features_t	sfeatures;
 	u32			msg_enable;
+	spinlock_t		addrs_lock; /* unused since backport of d3ba32162488 ("ipvlan: Make the addrs_lock be per port") */
 };
 
 struct ipvl_addr {
@@ -89,7 +90,6 @@ struct ipvl_port {
 	struct net_device	*dev;
 	possible_net_t		pnet;
 	struct hlist_head	hlhead[IPVLAN_HASH_SIZE];
-	spinlock_t		addrs_lock; /* guards hash-table and addrs */
 	struct list_head	ipvlans;
 	u16			mode;
 	u16			flags;
@@ -98,6 +98,9 @@ struct ipvl_port {
 	struct sk_buff_head	backlog;
 	int			count;
 	struct ida		ida;
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
+	spinlock_t		addrs_lock; /* guards hash-table and addrs */
+#endif
 };
 
 struct ipvl_skb_cb {
